    {
      "id": "4c9f36f54ac0897715e495d4817034ccd34293c0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-25 14:23:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, I'm not that experienced in that. could you please explain where/what should I add? thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "99f4e4a7b25d28b71e9b4fa5a8b7e2d74e3f6562",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-25 14:42:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nllverdev has been around for ages, so if there weren't previously problems with Debian, it may be that they don't need changes.\n\nIs there some reason to expect that this patch breaks Debian?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "315bbc7486adf552149ce76822dd255180168f5e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-25 15:53:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nActually its also RHEL spec file as well I'm worried about. Let me see if one of the other packages pulls it in.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ea1f99b70d6e5c6a24cf4545049a504a40088d93",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-25 16:11:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHistorically lustre has never properly supported dependencies for its rpms or debian packages.\n\nOkay I looked and it could potentially break rpm systems as well. So the problem is that as is if this patch landed it could be possible for a user that installed a prebuilt rpm and the system doesn't have libuuid installed. This would break for the user.\nEvery place in lustre.spec.in next to zlib you want to place libuuid. For zlib-devel you want to place libuuid-devel next to it. This will prevent any potential install issues.\n\nFor ubuntu you need to the do something similar. Hummm. I can push a patch that does this properly.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f288ede8e809e6823eddcbd3ad5fbe1e0ada339d",
      "author": {
